OL,6,FShe received treatment and was
OL,7,Fdischarged the following day. Her baby
OL,8,Fdid not sustain any injuries and was
OL,9,Fborn soon after the attack.
OL,11,FIn a statement read out in court, Miss
OL,12,FPintili, who attended the hearing,
OL,13,Fsaid she felt "lucky to be alive after
OL,14,Fthis harrowing experience", adding
OL,15,Fthat the attack had affected her
OL,16,Fsocially as she no longer feels
OL,17,Fconfident leaving the house.
